<topic id="preferences-editor-format-json">
  <title>JSON Preferences</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Preferences<indexterm>JSON formatting</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_mgp_bgk_54b">To configure the <uicontrol>JSON</uicontrol> format options, <ph
        conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/open-the-preferences-page"/> and go to <menucascade>
        <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Format</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>JSON</uicontrol>
      </menucascade>.</p>
    <p id="p_ngp_bgk_54b">The following option is available:</p>
    <p id="p_jsj_mbx_vcc"><uicontrol>Sort keys</uicontrol> - If enabled, when using the
        <uicontrol>Format and Indent</uicontrol> action on JSON content, dictionary items are sorted
      alphabetically by key name.</p>
  </body>
</topic>